                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.11/435: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-01-31T20:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 31, 1927—8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>38. Your telegram 76 of January 25, 4 p.m.<note n="4" xml:id="d243fn4">Not
                        printed.</note> You should inform consuls concerned that the authorization
                    granted to them to incur expenses actually necessary in the evacuation of
                    American citizens covers only additional expenditures such as demurrage for
                    vessels which may be essential in making transportation facilities available <pb
                        facs="0363" n="255" xml:id="pg_255"/> to endangered American citizens and
                    does not include ordinary charges for transportation such as the usual steamship
                    fares. If, however, any American citizen is unable to meet such ordinary charges
                    they may be defrayed for him on his written undertaking to refund the amounts as
                    soon as practicable. Inasmuch as funds for this purpose are limited, Department
                    must be promptly informed of all expenditures authorized.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
